# Domain layer — DDD

## Location and dependencies
- All domain code lives in `src/Context/{BoundedContext}/Domain/`.
- **No dependencies** on Symfony, Doctrine, or Application/Infrastructure. Only PHP and `src/Shared/Domain`.

## Aggregates
- Aggregate Root extends `App\Shared\Domain\AggregateRoot`.
- Relevant state changes are communicated with `$this->record(new XxxWasYyy(...))`.
- Use static factory methods for creation: `Aggregate::create(...)` and return the instance (do not construct from outside with bare `new` and no logic).

```php
// Good: factory method that records event
public static function create(AccountId $id, AccountCode $code, AccountName $name): self
{
    $account = new self($id->value(), $code->value(), $name->value());
    $account->record(new AccountWasCreated(...));
    return $account;
}
```

## Value Objects
- Immutable. Prefer `readonly` on properties.
- Validate in constructor; throw domain exception if value is invalid.
- Location: `Domain/` or `Domain/ValueObject/`. Descriptive names (e.g. `AccountCode`, `ExpenseDueDate`).

## Domain Events
- Classes in `Domain/Bus/`. Naming: `{Aggregate}Was{PastTenseAction}` (e.g. `AccountWasCreated`, `ExpenseWasEntered`).
- Extend the project's event base (e.g. `readonly class`, static `eventName()`, `fromPrimitives()` if reconstructed from EventStore).

## Repositories
- Only **interfaces** in Domain: `{AggregateName}Repository` (e.g. `AccountRepository`).
- Minimal methods needed: e.g. `save()`, `findOneByIdOrFail()`; do not expose persistence details.

## Domain exceptions
- In `Domain/Exception/`. Naming: `{Description}Exception` (e.g. `AccountNotFoundException`). Clear messages for debugging.
